This is a fair review.. It's a great film. It makes you feel like a kid when you watch it. Yes this trilogy was poorly handled with not being written by one source. But overall this film really pulls through in terms of rounding off this story. Fair play to J.J. almost, he really had a lose lose situation with this film. No matter what he did, some people were obviously not going to like it. (Like everything in star wars now, because the fanbase is so divided).
But the characters are great and the relationships between them all even more so. The story is strong, the visuals, costumes, music are all incredible (obviously).

I think Disney are well aware of the mistakes they've made on this trilogy and going forward they will change how they approach things. They have become very aware of how this fanbase works and I'm sure they will take that into account in the future.
